02:33.153 --> 02:35.988
Yo, Tommy! It's Ashley.

02:35.990 --> 02:38.657
I'm having some people over
tonight, if you wanna come over.

02:40.627 --> 02:41.760
No, I don't care.

02:41.762 --> 02:43.862
If you've got better things
to do, that's cool.

02:44.998 --> 02:46.532
Come on, man,
i just got back today.

02:46.534 --> 02:48.367
It's like a party, a good time.

02:49.769 --> 02:52.437
Come on.
Now, you owe me.

02:52.439 --> 02:54.940
And you can never come over to
my mom's house again, all right?

02:55.441 --> 02:55.440
You got it?

02:55.442 --> 02:58.410
You are officially banned
from the premises.

03:07.353 --> 03:08.854
Mom.

03:08.856 --> 03:09.988
This ain't a birthday party.

03:09.990 --> 03:11.123
I know that.

03:11.125 --> 03:12.824
Then why are you putting
candles on the cake?

03:12.826 --> 03:14.226
Candles are for celebrations.

03:18.231 --> 03:19.698
I'm not going to blow them out.

04:30.503 --> 04:32.738
- Hello, Ms. dottie.
- Ashley?

04:34.074 --> 04:35.707
When did you crawl out
of your hole?

04:35.709 --> 04:37.509
Why don't you try
being more positive?

04:37.877 --> 04:38.877
Hold up!

04:38.879 --> 04:40.545
You going to come up in my house

04:40.547 --> 04:43.015
and tell me I'm the one
who needs some positivity?

04:43.017 --> 04:44.850
You need a brain operation.

04:53.826 --> 04:54.760
Your booboo's back.

04:54.762 --> 04:56.328
No. Mm-mm.

04:56.330 --> 04:57.462
What d'you think,

04:57.464 --> 04:59.231
you can come back here
and have me again?

04:59.233 --> 05:01.466
You don't get the hint
when I don't pick up the phone?

05:01.468 --> 05:02.901
I have caller ID, you know?

05:02.903 --> 05:04.369
Look, I just wanted
to let you know

05:04.371 --> 05:06.338
that your baby boy
is back from his vacation.

05:07.173 --> 05:08.940
What you really want, trump?

05:08.942 --> 05:10.575
Hey, don't call me that.

05:10.577 --> 05:12.477
Hey, can dottie go back
on the side?

05:14.113 --> 05:15.747
- Um.
- Gotcha.

05:20.620 --> 05:22.521
Linda, I thought
about you everyday.

05:22.722 --> 05:22.721
So?

05:22.723 --> 05:25.824
I dreamt of your face
every time I closed my eyes.

05:25.826 --> 05:28.293
I was hoping
you thought of me, too.

05:28.295 --> 05:30.896
I'm back now, so we can finally
have some secret intimacy.

05:30.898 --> 05:33.899
I'm not interested in any type
of intimacies with you.

05:36.636 --> 05:39.204
I can't understand why
you feel this way, Linda.

05:39.206 --> 05:41.039
What did you expect,
i was gonna be like,

05:41.041 --> 05:43.975
"ooh, ash, now I ain't seen
or heard from you in forever.

05:43.977 --> 05:45.610
"I want you back"?

05:45.612 --> 05:48.013
I was just hoping you'd be
happy to see me, that's all.

05:48.015 --> 05:49.448
Happy to see you?

05:50.583 --> 05:52.851
You know, all this time
you've been gone,

05:52.853 --> 05:55.587
all this time, and I didn't
hear a word from you.

05:56.923 --> 05:59.024
You didn't write me
a letter or nothing.

05:59.026 --> 06:00.492
You don't know what
it's like in there...

06:00.494 --> 06:02.127
Let me tell you what it's like.

06:03.096 --> 06:04.596
When you're in love with someone

06:04.598 --> 06:06.264
and you're away from them,

06:06.266 --> 06:07.432
you write them a letter

06:07.434 --> 06:09.334
to tell them how much
you care about them.

06:09.336 --> 06:11.503
You sit down with a pencil
and some paper

06:11.505 --> 06:14.606
and you put into words
what you feel.

06:14.608 --> 06:16.508
You're supposed to learn this
like, in the third grade,

06:16.510 --> 06:17.609
but apparently, you didn't,

06:17.611 --> 06:19.444
because you were gone
for forever

06:19.446 --> 06:20.979
and I didn't hear a peep.

06:22.815 --> 06:23.982
I've moved on.

06:24.517 --> 06:25.917
I've got a man.

06:25.919 --> 06:27.085
Yes, she does.

06:27.087 --> 06:29.588
And I don't have time
to be moving backwards in life

06:29.590 --> 06:32.958
with somebody who is dumb
and always broke.

06:34.227 --> 06:35.727
Who's your new man, anyway?

06:36.095 --> 06:37.863
Dwayne.

06:37.865 --> 06:39.564
Dump truck Dwayne,
the garbage man?

06:39.566 --> 06:42.134
He may be a garbage man,
but he is good to me.

06:42.136 --> 06:43.735
You'd choose
the garbage man over me?

06:43.737 --> 06:45.737
What did I ever do to deserve
this type of treatment?

06:45.739 --> 06:46.739
What did you do?

06:48.007 --> 06:49.241
Do you want a list?

06:49.243 --> 06:50.942
Okay, how about the time
you tricked me

06:50.944 --> 06:52.744
into paying for your
other girlfriend's abortion?

06:52.746 --> 06:54.346
Are you going to bring that up?

06:54.348 --> 06:57.249
You're talking about the past,
I'm talking about the future.

06:57.251 --> 06:59.117
I'm talking about you and me.

06:59.119 --> 07:01.486
I'm talking about telling
the universe what you want

07:01.488 --> 07:02.654
and getting it.

07:02.656 --> 07:04.790
I'm talking about
the power of positivity.

07:06.392 --> 07:08.560
You are so boring.

07:12.465 --> 07:13.865
You can leave now.

07:14.767 --> 07:16.835
Okay, bye-bye.

07:16.837 --> 07:19.271
Okay, you can be like this now?

07:19.273 --> 07:22.340
But when dump truck Dwayne up and
leaves you for someone prettier,

07:22.342 --> 07:23.742
you're gonna be looking for me.

07:23.744 --> 07:25.277
You're gonna hunt me down.

07:25.279 --> 07:27.946
Okay, Ashley, you go ahead
and think positive.

08:21.601 --> 08:24.069
Don't you be digging up my yard!

08:25.371 --> 08:27.038
Mom, you haven't
seen it, have you?

08:27.040 --> 08:28.173
My toolbox.

08:28.175 --> 08:30.942
I ain't seen nothing,
but you digging up my grass.

08:30.944 --> 08:32.943
Why don't you
make yourself useful

08:32.946 --> 08:34.312
and do something I need?

08:34.313 --> 08:36.515
Like get rid of that old fridge?

08:36.517 --> 08:38.616
Mom, I can't move no fridge.

08:43.990 --> 08:46.558
Hey! Do you all need
a ladder up in there?

08:46.560 --> 08:47.626
It's a good deal.

08:47.628 --> 08:49.127
Nah, we're good.

08:52.000 --> 08:52.899
Hey!

08:52.900 --> 08:56.001
Hey, you guys!
Want a good deal on a ladder?

08:56.003 --> 08:58.637
We don't buy no
stolen goods, man!

08:58.639 --> 09:01.006
For you information,
my mother gave me this ladder.

09:01.008 --> 09:02.274
Thank you.

09:03.109 --> 09:05.310
Nice tall woman.

09:05.312 --> 09:08.246
Can I interest you in a ladder?

09:08.248 --> 09:10.348
Are you in need of a ladder?

09:17.590 --> 09:19.090
I'll help you.

09:22.328 --> 09:23.595
Lower it down.

09:26.766 --> 09:28.500
What is this,
a machine or something?

09:28.502 --> 09:30.068
Something like that.

09:30.070 --> 09:31.169
A respirator.

09:32.405 --> 09:33.538
What does it do?

09:33.540 --> 09:36.274
Nothing right now,
i got to get it fixed.

09:36.276 --> 09:37.709
Thanks for your help, though.

09:37.711 --> 09:39.010
Yeah, no problem.

09:39.579 --> 09:41.079
What's your name?

09:41.081 --> 09:42.280
Germs.

09:43.749 --> 09:44.749
Germs?

09:44.751 --> 09:46.351
Man, I'm not calling you, germs.

09:46.353 --> 09:47.919
- What's your real name.
- Jeremy.

09:47.921 --> 09:48.921
Nice!

09:49.488 --> 09:50.655
Hey, you need a ladder?

09:50.657 --> 09:51.923
No, I'm good.

09:51.925 --> 09:52.925
Right on, though.

09:53.492 --> 09:54.893
Yeah.

09:54.895 --> 09:55.895
No problem.

10:17.483 --> 10:19.351
Hey Jeremy, I need a favor.

10:20.252 --> 10:21.486
What are you doing?

10:21.488 --> 10:22.554
This your pickup?

10:22.556 --> 10:23.822
It's my granddad's.

10:23.824 --> 10:25.457
'Cause I was thinking,
since I helped you,

10:25.459 --> 10:26.791
maybe you should give me a hand.

10:26.793 --> 10:28.760
I would. Got somewhere
to be right now, though.

10:28.762 --> 10:30.929
Come on, I just need
the truck for like, an hour.

10:30.931 --> 10:33.231
Come on, man, get out of
my truck, I got swim lessons.

10:34.867 --> 10:36.234
I'll put my feet in the pool.

10:38.037 --> 10:41.506
Let's see who's the first
one to touch the wall.

10:41.508 --> 10:44.209
Who's the first one
to touch the wall?

10:45.678 --> 10:48.146
Usa wins! Usa!

11:20.681 --> 11:22.447
What is this?

11:22.449 --> 11:23.581
This is ulcer water?

11:23.583 --> 11:25.016
Yeah, give me that cup.

11:25.018 --> 11:25.950
You drink this?

11:25.952 --> 11:27.452
Don't worry about what I drink.

11:28.387 --> 11:30.221
Oh, man.

11:30.223 --> 11:31.956
That didn't go down right.

11:31.958 --> 11:33.892
I didn't tell you to drink it.

11:41.000 --> 11:43.568
Yeah, go on. Get that
hunk of junk outta here.

11:43.570 --> 11:44.869
Mom...

11:44.871 --> 11:46.871
Meet my new friend.

11:46.873 --> 11:48.540
Hi, Ms. Douglas,
I'm Jeremy.

11:48.542 --> 11:49.908
If you knew
what was good for you,

11:49.910 --> 11:51.943
you'd stay away from my son.

11:51.945 --> 11:54.112
Yeah, you'd probably
stay away from her, too.

11:54.114 --> 11:55.947
Well, maybe your new friend
can help you

11:55.949 --> 11:57.882
put them holes back
where they go.

12:00.052 --> 12:02.520
Buried something back here
long time ago,

12:02.522 --> 12:04.022
but can't find it now.

12:04.024 --> 12:06.291
My granddad has a metal detector,
if you want to borrow it.

12:06.293 --> 12:07.559
Yeah?

12:10.197 --> 12:12.697
- We're taking it now!
- -Good!

12:12.699 --> 12:13.998
You're welcome!

12:29.815 --> 12:31.449
You're dumping some stuff today?

12:31.451 --> 12:32.951
Thought you might be here.

12:33.385 --> 12:34.919
Hi, Ashley.

12:34.921 --> 12:36.988
Still being
a garbage man, I see.

12:37.890 --> 12:39.190
Yeah, well, just...

12:39.192 --> 12:40.959
Just trying to
make a living, man.

12:42.027 --> 12:44.062
Y'all try to drop
this stuff off?

12:44.064 --> 12:45.430
Just this fridge in the back.

12:46.232 --> 12:47.365
And the ladder?

12:47.367 --> 12:48.466
Ladder's for sale.

12:49.502 --> 12:50.702
You've dumped here before?

12:50.704 --> 12:52.804
No, I don't frequent
garbage places.

12:55.574 --> 12:57.075
Fill up this form, please.

12:59.812 --> 13:01.880
Heard you've been
running around with Linda.

13:03.115 --> 13:04.482
That's between me and her.

13:04.484 --> 13:05.717
All right, I notice

13:05.719 --> 13:07.585
you put on some weight
since I last saw you.

13:07.587 --> 13:09.120
How do you wanna pay the fee?

13:09.488 --> 13:10.488
Fee? What fee?

13:11.090 --> 13:12.824
There's a $100 Hazmat fee

13:12.826 --> 13:14.459
for the disposal
of refrigerators.

13:14.461 --> 13:17.195
So we got to pay you
$100 to throw something out?

13:20.499 --> 13:24.068
"Freon used as a refrigerant
is a hazardous material"

13:24.070 --> 13:26.638
"and there is special handling
involved in its disposal."

13:26.640 --> 13:29.140
"The county has assessed
a $100 fee"

13:29.142 --> 13:31.209
"to account for
this special handling."

13:33.913 --> 13:35.880
Now, I don't have a $100 on me.

13:35.882 --> 13:38.216
You want to give me
your fridge or not?

13:38.218 --> 13:40.652
I got the money,
you got to pay me back, though.

13:40.654 --> 13:42.053
Yeah? No problem.

13:42.055 --> 13:43.454
We'll get my mom
to pay you back.

13:43.923 --> 13:45.223
We got your money.

13:50.563 --> 13:51.563
All right.

13:52.731 --> 13:54.432
You're good
to drop off the fridge.

13:54.434 --> 13:56.968
You know, let me know
when you get tired of Linda.

13:56.970 --> 13:58.203
I'll take over.

14:00.639 --> 14:02.373
Ashley's back, baby.

14:03.475 --> 14:05.944
Man, how can she be
in love with that dude?

14:05.946 --> 14:06.978
Who would you rather have,

14:06.980 --> 14:08.746
me or that dude with the papers?

14:08.748 --> 14:10.148
I'm not getting into that.

14:12.718 --> 14:14.185
Where do you get
your money from?

14:14.486 --> 14:15.787
Work.

14:15.789 --> 14:17.789
- You don't work.
- I work.

14:17.791 --> 14:20.091
I do work for a medical
science company.

14:20.659 --> 14:23.728
Like what?
Test tube babies?

14:23.730 --> 14:25.129
No, really. I mean,
i don't know.

14:25.131 --> 14:26.798
Just test out new products.

14:26.800 --> 14:28.066
What kind of products?

14:29.034 --> 14:31.536
It varies. Everything from...

14:31.538 --> 14:33.938
Putting a tampon on my back,

14:33.940 --> 14:36.808
or try some new toilet paper.

14:36.810 --> 14:39.177
One time, they cut off
my pinky toe,

14:39.179 --> 14:41.279
and reattached it with a laser.

14:42.915 --> 14:44.249
Are you serious?

14:45.417 --> 14:47.886
Right now, I'm testing out
these new patches.

14:50.055 --> 14:51.723
I would never do this.

14:51.725 --> 14:53.458
Be some sort of lab rat.

14:53.460 --> 14:55.660
It helps them make medicine.

14:55.662 --> 14:57.262
How do you make your money?

14:57.264 --> 14:58.630
Rusty old ladders?

15:02.968 --> 15:05.336
You're not a very good swimmer,
are you?

15:05.338 --> 15:07.906
Not right now,
but I'll get there.

15:07.908 --> 15:09.508
You can hold your breath
for a long time?

15:09.842 --> 15:11.676
Not really.

15:11.678 --> 15:12.944
Got this weird disease

15:12.946 --> 15:15.380
where my lungs won't take
the oxygen I breath.

15:15.382 --> 15:17.582
Runs in the family,
my granddad got it, too.

15:19.551 --> 15:20.518
He's an inventor.

15:20.520 --> 15:21.486
People think he crazy,

15:21.488 --> 15:23.221
but he's the smartest man
in the world.

15:24.256 --> 15:27.358
I know this guy who could
hold his breath for forever.

15:27.993 --> 15:29.193
He can control his heart rate,

15:29.195 --> 15:30.595
body temperature,
he can control everything.

15:30.597 --> 15:32.530
- Yeah right.
- Yeah, he showed me.

15:32.532 --> 15:35.500
Had me grab his hands
and he held his breath.

15:35.502 --> 15:37.936
And I could feel his hands
getting colder, like ice cold.

15:38.737 --> 15:40.438
I've been working on it myself.

15:40.440 --> 15:42.440
I could hold my breath
longer than you.

15:42.442 --> 15:43.474
I believe that.

15:45.477 --> 15:47.178
On a count of three.

15:47.180 --> 15:50.048
- One, two, three...
- Let me stop chewing.

15:54.987 --> 15:56.988
Hold it, there goes my aunt.

16:28.320 --> 16:31.222
Yeah, who's that?
I see her butt from here.

16:31.224 --> 16:32.991
How you gonna talk
about my aunt like that?

16:32.993 --> 16:34.926
- She got a man?
- No...

16:34.928 --> 16:37.161
She used to have this
cold cut take care of her.

16:37.163 --> 16:38.663
Does she work at a donut?

16:38.665 --> 16:39.664
For the time being.

16:39.666 --> 16:41.099
She wanna be
a stay-at-home mom.

16:41.101 --> 16:42.633
What happened to her man?

16:42.635 --> 16:43.935
Got into a bad car accident.

16:43.937 --> 16:46.137
He got paralyzed
from the waist up.

16:46.139 --> 16:47.505
You can't paralyze
from the waist up.

16:47.507 --> 16:48.439
I'm telling you he was!

16:48.441 --> 16:50.174
How, how are you
going to be like that?

16:50.176 --> 16:51.042
Look.

16:51.044 --> 16:52.677
See, his legs still work.

16:52.679 --> 16:54.412
But he was bent over like this.

16:55.714 --> 16:56.948
Wait, wait...

16:56.950 --> 16:59.317
You think she would get me
if I walked around like that?

16:59.319 --> 17:00.618
Hey, honey, let me take you out.

17:00.620 --> 17:02.587
I don't think about that, man.
That's my aunt.

17:02.589 --> 17:03.755
Now, you know what I mean?

17:04.823 --> 17:06.156
She looking for a man?

17:25.944 --> 17:27.310
Why don't you
take your shirt off?

17:27.613 --> 17:28.813
Mmm.

17:28.815 --> 17:30.248
No, I'm good.

17:32.751 --> 17:33.818
I wanna look at you.

17:35.354 --> 17:36.921
- No. No!
- I wanna look at you.

17:36.923 --> 17:37.989
No!

17:37.991 --> 17:39.490
- I wanna look at you.
- Oh...

17:39.492 --> 17:41.359
They look weird
when I'm laying down.

17:41.361 --> 17:42.627
They're looking good to me.

17:44.297 --> 17:45.029
Stop!

17:45.031 --> 17:47.131
Get, get from under there!

18:11.023 --> 18:12.790
I got something
i got to tell you about.

18:13.692 --> 18:14.692
Okay...

18:15.027 --> 18:16.194
What?

18:17.930 --> 18:20.364
I'm in love with somebody else.

18:20.366 --> 18:23.134
I've been in love with this girl
since the first day I saw her.

18:28.140 --> 18:29.440
Is that all right with you?

18:32.144 --> 18:33.478
She your girlfriend
or something?

18:35.013 --> 18:36.214
Mmm...

18:37.616 --> 18:39.817
So right now, she's got
a different situation.

18:43.255 --> 18:44.789
So why are you
telling me about her?

18:47.759 --> 18:49.327
I don't know, I like you.

18:51.096 --> 18:52.296
You're looking good,

18:53.031 --> 18:54.398
you got a fine butt.

18:58.504 --> 19:00.238
But I'm always gonna
love me some Linda.

19:03.175 --> 19:04.509
She got a hold on me.

19:08.614 --> 19:10.348
But she just won't
love me anymore.

19:20.325 --> 19:21.592
So you wanna be my girl?

19:50.155 --> 19:51.656
Hey! How are you doin',
Ms. Douglas?

19:51.658 --> 19:52.690
